# The `FastISel` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

This is a fast-path instruction selection class that generates poor code and doesn&#39;t support illegal types or non-trivial lowering, but runs quickly. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Declaration

<CodeBlock>class llvm::FastISel</CodeBlock>

## Description {#details}

This is a fast-path instruction selection class that generates poor code and doesn&#39;t support illegal types or non-trivial lowering, but runs quickly.

Definition at line 66 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/fastisel-h">FastISel.h</a>.

### tryToFoldLoad() {#a5a81ca548cc88df15a58aed766bdd890}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool FastISel::tryToFoldLoad (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loadinst">LoadInst</a> &#42; LI, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction">Instruction</a> &#42; FoldInst)</>}>
We&#39;re checking to see if we can fold <code>LI</code> into <code>FoldInst</code>.

Note that we could have a sequence where multiple LLVM IR instructions are folded into the same machineinstr. For example we could have:

A: x = load i32 &#42;P B: y = icmp A, 42 C: br y, ...

In this scenario, <code>LI</code> is &quot;A&quot;, and <code>FoldInst</code> is &quot;C&quot;. We know about &quot;B&quot; (and any other folded instructions) because it is between A and C.

If we succeed folding, return true.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/fastisel-h/#l00292">292</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/fastisel-h">FastISel.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/lib/codegen/selectiondag/fastisel-cpp/#l02315">2315</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/lib/codegen/selectiondag/fastisel-cpp">FastISel.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
